-- Chuquicamata Workers Accept 3.7% Pay Rise, Tercera Says
-- B y   M a t t h e w   B r i s t o w
-- 2012-12-16T15:13:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-16/chuquicamata-workers-accept-3-7-pay-rise-tercera-says.html
Workers at Codelco’s Chuquicamata
copper mine in  Chile  accepted the company’s offer of a 16.8
million peso bonus ($35,400), an interest free loan of 3 million
pesos, and a 3.7 percent salary increase, La Tercera  reported ,
citing union leader Armando Silva.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Matthew Bristow in Bogota at 
 mbristow5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Attwood at 
 jattwood3@bloomberg.net  